<span class="s1">&lt;td&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame object for representing 2D bitmasks</span><span class="s1">&lt;/td&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Useful for fast pixel perfect collision detection. A mask uses 1 bit per-pixel</span>
<span class="s0">to store which parts collide.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">Creates a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.mask.Mask&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">object from the given surface by setting all the</span>
<span class="s0">opaque pixels and not setting the transparent pixels.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If the surface uses a color-key, then it is used to decide which bits in</span>
<span class="s0">the resulting mask are set. All the pixels that are </span><span class="s1">&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">not</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">equal to the</span>
<span class="s0">color-key are </span><span class="s1">&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">set</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">and the pixels equal to the color-key are not set.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">If a color-key is not used, then the alpha value of each pixel is used to</span>
<span class="s0">decide which bits in the resulting mask are set. All the pixels that have an</span>
<span class="s0">alpha value </span><span class="s1">&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">greater than</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">threshold</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter are </span><span class="s1">&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">set</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">and the</span>
<span class="s0">pixels with an alpha value less than or equal to the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">threshold</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">are</span>
<span class="s0">not set.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">(</span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.Surface&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;em&gt;</span><span class="s0">Surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;</span><span class="s0">) -- the surface to create the mask from</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">This is a more featureful method of getting a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.mask.Mask&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">from a surface.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/table&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">object is used to represent a 2D bitmask. Each bit in</span>
<span class="s0">the mask represents a pixel. 1 is used to indicate a set bit and 0 is used</span>
<span class="s0">to indicate an unset bit. Set bits in a mask can be used to detect collisions</span>
<span class="s0">with other masks and their set bits.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A filled mask has all of its bits set to 1, conversely an</span>
<span class="s0">unfilled/cleared/empty mask has all of its bits set to 0. Masks can be</span>
<span class="s0">created unfilled (default) or filled by using the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">fill</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter. Masks</span>
<span class="s0">can also be cleared or filled using the </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask.clear&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.mask.Mask.clear()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sets all bits to 0</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask.fill&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-func docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">pygame.mask.Mask.fill()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;tooltip-content&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Sets all bits to 1</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">methods respectively.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s0">then it should override the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">__copy__()</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">method. <span class="s0">copy the required data as in the following example code.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;dd&gt;&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line-block&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;summaryline&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns a mask containing a connected component</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">connected_component() -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;line&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;signature&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">connected_component(pos) -</span><span class="s4">&amp;gt; </span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">A connected component is a group (1 or more) of connected set bits</span>
<span class="s0">(orthogonally and diagonally). The SAUF algorithm, which checks 8 point</span>
<span class="s0">connectivity, is used to find a connected component in the mask.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">By default this method will return a </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.mask.Mask&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">containing the largest</span>
<span class="s0">connected component in the mask. Optionally, a bit coordinate can be</span>
<span class="s0">specified and the connected component containing it will be returned. If</span>
<span class="s0">the bit at the given location is not set, the returned </span><span class="s1">&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;#pygame.mask.Mask&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.mask.Mask&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;xref py py-class docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Mask</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; </span><span class="s0">will</span>
<span class="s0">be empty (no bits set).</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dl </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-list simple&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Parameters</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>

<span class="s0">bit at this position</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>

<span class="s1">&lt;/ul&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Returns</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter (or a newly created surface if no</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter was provided) with this mask drawn on it</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Return type</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-odd&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;reference internal&quot; </span><span class="s2">href</span><span class="s3">=&quot;surface.html#pygame.Surface&quot; </span><span class="s2">title</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pygame.Surface&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dt </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Raises</span><span class="s1">&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;colon&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">:</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/dt&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;dd </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;field-even&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;</span><span class="s0">ValueError</span><span class="s1">&lt;/strong&gt; </span><span class="s0">-- if the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">setsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter or </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unsetsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span>
<span class="s0">parameter does not have the same format (bytesize/bitsize/alpha) as</span>
<span class="s0">the </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">surface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dd&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/dl&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition-title&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">To skip drawing the set bits, both </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">setsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">setcolor</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">must</span>
<span class="s0">be </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. The </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">setsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter defaults to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, but</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">setcolor</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">defaults to a color value and therefore must be set to</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;div </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition note&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;admonition-title&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">Note</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;p&gt;</span><span class="s0">To skip drawing the unset bits, both </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unsetsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">and</span>
<span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unsetcolor</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">must be </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">. The </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unsetsurface</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">parameter</span>
<span class="s0">defaults to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">, but </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">unsetcolor</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt; </span><span class="s0">defaults to a color value and</span>
<span class="s0">therefore must be set to </span><span class="s1">&lt;code </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;docutils literal notranslate&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;&lt;span </span><span class="s2">class</span><span class="s3">=&quot;pre&quot;</span><span class="s1">&gt;</span><span class="s0">None</span><span class="s1">&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;</span><span class="s0">.</span><span class="s1">&lt;/p&gt;</span>
